"title": "5934: restraint",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5934: restraint",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The holding back of actions, emotions or forces, whether one's own or another's. God holds back the power and extent of evil in the world and restrains his anger. Believers are to show similar self-control in life, especially in speech.</p>\n<h2>Restraint as the holding back of actions</h2>\n<h3>The example of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:52-Matt26:53\">MAT 26:52–26:53</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Other examples</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:6\">EXO 36:6</a> <em>God restrains the Israelites</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:13\">1SA 3:13</a> <em>Eli's failure to restrain his sons</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:1-1Sam24:22\">1SA 24:1–24:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:1-1Sam26:25\">1SA 26:1–26:25</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:6\">1KI 1:6</a> <em>David's failure to restrain Adonijah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:10\">EST 5:10</a> <em>Haman's self-restraint</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:10\">JER 14:10</a> <em>Judah's lack of restraint</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:16\">2PE 2:16</a> <em>Balaam's donkey</em></p>\n<h2>Restraint as the holding back of emotions</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's silence under suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21-1Pet2:23\">1PE 2:21–2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:62-Matt26:63\">MAT 26:62–26:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:60-Mark14:61\">MRK 14:60–14:61</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:12-Matt27:14\">MAT 27:12–27:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:4-Mark15:5\">MRK 15:4–15:5</a></p>\n<h2>Restraint as the holding back of forces</h2>\n<h3>God and the Red Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:21\">EXO 14:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:8\">EXO 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:13\">PSA 78:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ and the wind and the waves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:23-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:23–8:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:36-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:36–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:22-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:22–8:25</a></p>\n<h2>God restrains the power of evil</h2>\n<h3>In the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:20\">MRK 13:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:22\">MAT 24:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:28\">2KI 19:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:10\">PSA 76:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:6-2Thess2:7\">2TH 2:6–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">REV 20:2</a></p>\n<h3>From the righteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:15\">JHN 17:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:39\">1SA 25:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:10\">1CH 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:13\">PSA 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:7\">PSA 34:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:3\">PSA 141:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:13\">MAT 6:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:3\">REV 7:3</a></p>\n<h2>God restrains his anger</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:38\">PSA 78:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6\">EXO 34:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:18\">NUM 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:17\">NEH 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:11\">PSA 74:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:15\">PSA 86:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:8\">PSA 103:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:8\">PSA 145:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:9\">ISA 48:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">JOL 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:2\">JON 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are to show restraint</h2>\n<h3>In their speech</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:3\">PSA 141:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:26\">JAS 1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:1\">PSA 39:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:3\">PRO 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:23\">PRO 21:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:2-Jas3:12\">JAS 3:2–3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:10\">1PE 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:13\">PSA 34:13</a></p>\n<h3>In their actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:9\">PSA 32:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12\">ROM 6:12</a></p>",
